HISTORY and Features of Java
http://www.javatpoint.com/history-of-java

Green Team started Java. This new language is for digital devices such as setter box, television etc
Firstly, it was called "Greentalk" by James Gosling and file extension was .gt.
After that, it was called Oak and was developed as a part of the Green project.
They wanted something that reflected the essence of the technology: revolutionary, dynamic, lively, cool, unique, and easy to spell and fun to say.Hence came up with Java
Java means Coffee. Hence java has a coffee symbol


Feature
http://www.javatpoint.com/features-of-java

Simple : Syntax is based on C++, removed rarely used feature, unreferenced object need not be used
Platform Independent : build once run anywhere
Secure : Java checks all memory access and also makes sure no virus are communicated.
Robust: has strong memory management, no pointers are used, There is automatic garbage collection. Exception and type checking is easy.
Architectural Neutral : There is no platform dependent features in Java
Portable : TO any platform
High Performance : Java is faster than native interpreter, because byte code is in native language
Distributed : we can access any file from the machine using the method
